            "id": "4431888",
            "title": "Pinterest reportedly wanted to buy an ad tech company to ramp up sales",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\">Pinterest had apparently thought of spending hundreds of millions on buying an advertising technology firm to boost its ad sales.</p>\n<p>According to a Wednesday report from <em>The Information</em>, citing a source, the company had considered such a move in January, but since the fourth quarter of last year, it's been testing an ad sales tie-up with Index Exchange and Criteo (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CRTO\" title=\"Criteo S.A.\">CRTO</a></span>).</p>\n<p> A spokesperson for the company told the tech news outlet the company had “made no acquisition offers but [is] always evaluating new ways to drive results for advertisers, including partnerships with ad tech firms.”</p>\n<p>Kamran Ansari, former head of corporate development at Pinterest between 2015 and 2018, said the company previously considered buying ad tech firms because doing so had helped other consumer technology companies grow.</p>\n<p>“The way that Meta (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/META\" title=\"Meta Platforms, Inc.\">META</a>) and Google (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOG\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOG</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOGL\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOGL</a>) kind of leapfrogged everyone else and advanced their companies 10, 15 years ago was [through] aggressive and significant M&amp;A,” Ansari reportedly said. He added that when Pinterest was looking for potential target companies to buy, there weren’t any that looked appealing.</p>\n<p>The report also said the company worked with two ad tech firms to sell ad space between 2017 and 2018, which didn't generate much revenue, while ads were produced in low quality, or \"blurry images sold at low prices.\"</p>\n<p>The image-sharing platform is also on the hunt to hire a vice president of programmatic advertising, a source familiar with the company's plans told <em>The Info</em>, while another source said it wants to hire a head of mergers and acquisitions.</p>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1146250510/image_1146250510.jpg?io=getty-c-w750",
